         <abstract>
            <p>A linear nonconforming (conforming) displacement finite element method for the pure displacement (pure traction) problem in two-dimensional linear elasticity for a homogeneous isotropic elastic material is considered. In the case of a convex polygonal configuration domain, O(h) (O(h&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)) error estimates in the energy (L&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;) norm are obtained. The convergence rate does not deteriorate for nearly incompressible material. Furthermore, the convergence analysis does not rely on the theory of saddle point problems.</p>
          </abstract>
